@mattyb149 I've been thinking about what to do with this PR, and I think it needs to be put into a new NAR. I'm thinking "nifi-elasticsearch-restapi.nar" or something like that. What I'd ideally like to do is position this to be a new package that does full CRUD using only the official REST API from Elastic Co.

It might also help with the issue that @joewitt raised about the sizing because the current mix of ElasticSearch processors use different toolkits which needlessly raises the size of the NARs.

Thoughts?

I see. So the issue is with this annotation?

    @ApiModelProperty(
            value = "The state of the processor.",
            allowableValues = "RUNNING, STOPPED, DISABLED, INVALID"
    )

Please open a new ticket. This ticket has already been released and cannot be re-opened now.
